A mentally challenged Helenvale teenager has been missing since Friday and police have appealed for assistance in tracing his whereabouts. Sixteen-year-old Shelton  Afrikaner left his Elk Street home at about 2pm wearing blue shorts, a blue T-shirt, a black K-Way top, a blue hooded top, and white and blue Tommy takkies. According to his family, his mental functioning was that of a 10-year-old,  police spokesperson Colonel Priscilla Naidu said. Contact Detective Ayanda Songxaba on 071-352-4733 if you have seen Shelton or may know where he is. HeraldLIVE